ell with the model and the `SQLAlchemy` cascade settings. This means that with a simple hard delete we get full deletion, so I now need to think about how to appropriately handle the soft archive status. This would let us also set the status field to 'archived'. And, I need to confirm access restrictions.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n94 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T11:39:58.844Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Securing Client Route Access**\\n\\nI've confirmed that the `clients.py` route file, with the `current_user: User = Depends(require_admin)` dependency, is perfectly secure and RBAC compliant. This ensures client portal users cannot list or manipulate all clients. I'm now drafting the `backend/app/api/routes/clients.py` file, and am considering query parameter filtering. I am looking at filtering by search and status. I will work on this next.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n95 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T11:39:59.496Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"usage\",\"inputTokens\":27118,\"outputTokens\":1469,\"cacheReadTokens\":16792,\"cost\":0.0312288,\"totalInputTokens\":228508,\"totalOutputTokens\":5352,\"totalCacheReadTokens\":112455,\"totalCost\":0.23911575000000002}}\n\n[Showing lines 1-95 of 150. Use start_line/end_line to read other sections.]","success":true},{"query":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/automation/logs/2026-06-27T11-44-13-003Z-133-phase5-api-clients-crud-validation.log:1-150","result":"  1 | ## npm run lint\n  2 | exit=0\n  3 | STDOUT:\n  4 | \n  5 | > hirezapp_landing_page@0.1.0 lint\n  6 | > eslint\n  7 | \n  8 | \n  9 | STDERR:\n 10 | \n 11 | \n 12 | ## npm run build\n 13 | exit=0\n 14 | STDOUT:\n 15 | \n 16 | > hirezapp_landing_page@0.1.0 build\n 17 | > next build\n 18 | \n 19 | ▲ Next.js 16.2.9 (Turbopack)\n 20 | - Environments: .env\n 21 | \n 22 |   Creating an optimized production build ...\n 23 | ✓ Compiled successfully i