{"ts":"2026-06-27T11:47:32.594Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"c4c4de55","input":{"summary":"### Investigation, Implementation and Resolution Summary\n\n#### 1. Files Changed/Created\n- `backend/app/api/routes/__init__.py`: Registered and mounted the clients sub-router with prefix `/clients` and tags `[\"clients\"]`.\n- `backend/app/api/routes/clients.py`: Implemented robust CRUD endpoints with `require_admin` role-based protection for the Admin ClientAccount:\n  - `GET /api/v1/clients`: Supports multi-field searching (name, industry, region, owner), specific filters (status, industry, region), and pagination.\n  - `GET /api/v1/clients/{client_id}`: Retrieves individual tenant details; returns `404 Not Found` if missing.\n  - `POST /api/v1/clients`: Creates brand new client records with duplicate name validation (raises `400 Bad Request` if name exists) and registers the event in SystemLoggerService.\n  - `PATCH /api/v1/clients/{client_id}`: Partially updates client fields and logs the action.\n  - `DELETE /api/v1/clients/{client_id}`: Soft-archives client by setting `status = \"archived\"` by default, or performs a complete hard database deletion when query parameter `hard_delete=True` is provided.\n- `backend/app/test_clients_api.py`: Implemented exhaustive integration tests for all ClientAccount CRUD endpoints including search, creation duplicate handling, updates, soft archives, and hard deletions.\n\n#### 2. Validation Performed\n- Ran Python backend security tests via `backend/venv/bin/python backend/app/test_security_utilities.py` which completed successfully with all assertions passing.\n- Ran ClientAccount integration tests via `backend/venv/bin/python backend/app/test_clients_api.py` which completed successfully with all assertions passing.\n- Ran frontend code quality checks using `npm run lint`, resulting in a perfect execution with no linting errors.\n\n#### 3. Limitations\n- Backend operations utilize a SQLAlchemy session. In a production deployment, authenticating the `current_user` will require standard bearer token header injection, which is simulated here using MockUser/require_admin dependency injectables.","verified":true}}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T11:47:32.596Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"c4c4de55","output":"Submission recorded (verified): ### Investigation, Implementation and Resolution Summary\n\n#### 1. Files Changed/Created\n- `backend/app/api/routes/__init__.py`: Registered and mounted the clients sub-router with prefix `/clients` and tags `[\"clients\"]`.\n- `backend/app/api/routes/clients.py`: Implemented robust CRUD endpoints with `require_admin` role-based protection for the Admin ClientAccount:\n  - `GET /api/v1/clients`: Supports multi-field searching (name, industry, region, owner), specific filters (status, industry, region), and pagination.\n  - `GET /api/v1/clients/{client_id}`: Retrieves individual tenant details; returns `404 Not Found` if missing.\n  - `POST /api/v1/clients`: Creates brand new client records with duplicate name validation (raises `400 Bad Request` if name exists) and registers the event in SystemLoggerService.\n  - `PATCH /api/v1/clients/{client_id}`: Partially updates client fields and logs the action.\n  - `DELETE /api/v1/clients/{client_id}`: Soft-archives client by setting `status = \"archived\"` by default, or performs a complete hard database deletion when query parameter `hard_delete=True` is provided.\n- `backend/app/test_clients_api.py`: Implemented exhaustive integration tests for all ClientAccount CRUD endpoints including search, creation duplicate handling, updates, soft archives, and hard deletions.\n\n#### 2. Validation Performed\n- Ran Python backend security tests via `backend/venv/bin/python backend/app/test_security_utilities.py` which completed successfully with all assertions passing.\n- Ran ClientAccount integration tests via `backend/venv/bin/python backend/app/test_clients_api.py` which completed successfully with all assertions passing.\n- Ran frontend code quality checks using `npm run lint`, resulting in a perfect execution with no linting error